); IV with 3 major sense cones, VIII small but distinct from VII. Pronotum transverse, with 5 pairs of long blunt setae, am slightly longer than aa; surface almost smooth, with weak sculpture near margins. Fore femora not enlarged. Fore wing with 3 blunt sub-basal setae arising in straight line, almost equal in length, with about 10 duplicated cilia. Mesonotum transversely reticulate, lateral setae well-developed, blunt. Metanotum sculptured with longitudinal stripes, major setae slender and acute. Mesopresternum paired lateral triangles weakly connected medially (

), metathoracic sternopleural sutures short. Pelta broadly triangular, weakly reticulate, with a pair of CPS (

); tergite II with 3 pairs of lateral setae; tergite VIII posterolateral setae well-developed, slightly shorter than posteroangulars; tergite IX setae S1–S3 about as long as tube, acute at apex (

